name: Mixy

Live out your DJ dreams with Mixy, the mind-blowing music app that lets you mash-up any song in seconds.

⁕ Add your songs
⁕ Instantly blend vocals and beats
⁕ Play and share your mashup anywhere

There’s no limit to your imagination!

name: Digipals
long_description:
Social media has become more media and less social. When I open up Facebook and Instagram, I don’t see any of my friends on it anymore - it’s one third ads, one third content from strangers on the internet, and one third AI slop. My friends are no longer on social media - I either meet up with them IRL or catch up with them in group chats.

Launch Video
https://youtu.be/KW2tjLl6sxM 

We’re building the future of social in the age of AI where digipals (ambient ai agents that have full context over your location, calendar, group chats, photos, and relationship history with your friends) act as the atomic units of human coordination. Your digipal gets full context over who you are, when you're available, and what you like. It then talks with your friends’ digipals to suggest hangouts when everyone is free, find restaurants and coffee shops nearby, make dinner reservations using AI calls, split bills based on the receipt, and nudge posting photo memories after hanging out.

By removing the friction for human connection, we believe that AI can be used to deepen human relationships by allowing us to spend more time with friends IRL and through staying close to their life updates and memories in group chats.
one_liner: Building the Future of Social in the Age of AI

name: Efference
long_description: Efference builds the eyes and visual cortex for robots. Instead of treating depth as a hardware problem, we use software — inspired by how humans see — to generate rich and reliable 3D information. This lets us deliver higher performance and greater ease of use at a lower price than existing stereo cameras.
one_liner: We build the eyes and visual cortex for robots.

name: Lapis

name: Semiotic
long_description:
Semiotic is an AI‑native design firm built to deliver human‑quality work at a significantly higher speed and scale than traditional design agencies.

name: Remedy

name: Brickanta
long_description: Cursor for construction estimation & project management. Brickanta analyzes estimates and project details to help automate admin work, reduce errors and inaccuracy, and accelerate delivery with AI trained on the standardized building protocols.
one_liner: Cursor for construction estimation & project management

name: AirCaps
long_description:
AirCaps is bringing AI assistance to in-person conversations. 

Our AI-copilot provides live captions, translations, AI meeting notes and insights for in-person conversations in real-time. It's deployed as an app for lightweight AR glasses so you can see visual information overlaid onto your field of vision.

You can think of it like a Zoom AI meeting assistant or Granola, but for in-person conversations, and with the ability to proactively help you in real-time, not just after the conversation.

We’re building the capture and intelligence layer for the 216 billion daily conversations that happen face-to-face.

We’ve already processed 16,500 hours of real-world conversations and counting. Today, AirCaps assists with 11% of our users’ in-person conversations.

We did $93K in revenue in October and grew 6.5x from September while spending <$3K on marketing (and hit $70K in revenue in the first 2 weeks of November). Our power users average 6h+ daily usage and our day-30 retention is 91%.

We previously went viral (75M+ views on TikTok, 150K+ followers) and have been featured by The New Yorker, WIRED, and Forbes.

Madhav (CEO, Yale CS) has been building in audio and AR since age 13, starting with Google Glass apps and voice assistants for Raspberry Pis. He researched audio AI at the MIT Media Lab. Nirbhay (CTO, Cornell CS) built voice AI on smart glasses in high school and built conversational AI products as the first engineer at 2 YC startups.
one_liner: The AI copilot for in-person conversations.

name: Uplane
long_description:
Uplane uses AI to automate digital advertising.

Uplane's AI platform creates thousands of ad campaigns with matching landing pages for each one, and allocates budgets across Meta, Google, TikTok and more. By connecting to CRM and ERP data, Uplane learns what drives profit and continuously improves campaigns.

Companies waste billions on bad ads, mismatched landing pages, and poor budget allocation. Uplane fixes this by replacing a patchwork of agencies, spreadsheets, and siloed tools with one self-improving system. The result: 20-50% higher ROAS for enterprises and effortless, expert-level marketing for SMBs.

Digital marketing is a $740B market with a 10% CAGR. Uplane charges a base fee plus up to 10% of ad spend, outperforming marketing agencies that typically charge 10-30%.

The team has deep founder-market fit: Julius managed a 7-digit monthly ad budget at one of the biggest ad spenders in Europe; Marvin has an academic background in Data Science (Imperial, Harvard) and led growth analytics & operations at a unicorn; Lukas was Head of Engineering at two YC startups, Blair (S19) and Fastgen (W23).
one_liner: Automate digital advertising with AI

name: Structured AI
long_description: Structured AI understands building codes, standards, drawing, and project requirements to generate and update the technical documents that normally take weeks to complete. Its AI agents live inside software tools like Revit, Word, Excel, and SharePoint that mechanical, electrical, civil, and structural engineers already use.
one_liner: AI workforce for construction design engineering

name: Parse
long_description: Parse lets developers build APIs for any website in seconds at fractions of a cent per call. Unlike traditional scraping tools that rely on slow, expensive headless browsers, Parse reverse-engineers websites' underlying network requests and generates optimized API endpoints automatically. This makes Parse 10-100x faster and significantly cheaper than browser automation, enabling use cases like real-time price monitoring, lead generation, and data integration that were previously impractical.

name: Brickwise
long_description:
We've built an AI property manager that automates maintenance for Landlord's and Property Managers. Brickwise handles tenant calls and messages 24/7, following up by chasing contractors and resolving payments.

This provides higher tenant satisfaction, while also simplifying the workloads of property managers. Our property manager operates across all communication channels, including SMS, WhatsApp, phone calls, and email, making it easy to integrate with existing workflows.

name: Zavo

Zavo is the first AI-point of sale platform for restaurants.

From reservations, to payments to point of sale, we have built the full restaurant tech stack in-house with AI automation across all products.

name: Sylvian

Sylvian creates expert data for LLMs through competitions.

LLMs continue to need lots of expert data. Unfortunately, existing data vendors like Scale or Mercor are not motivating the best experts through part-time pay. Competitions are more intrinsic motivators, and naturally incentivize high quality data.

Sylvian creates expert data for LLMs through competitions, starting with tool use data (e.g. Excel, VSCode). We already have 4,500+ experts, from IMO Golds to MIT/Stanford PhDs to full time QRs at Point72, producing data at 1B tokens/week!

name: Nexus
long_description: Nexus enables non-technical teams in large organizations to build production-ready AI agents without code. $900k ARR

name: Bolna AI
long_description:
Bolna handles the complexity of voice infra, so enterprises can automate calls faster, better, and cheaper, at scale

Bolna is a Voice AI Orchestration platform purpose-built for Indian enterprises.
Businesses in India run tens of thousands of calls every day - across sales, support, collections, recruitment, and more. Bolna gives them the power to build and deploy Voice AI Agents directly from their transcripts and FAQs, so they can start automating calls immediately.

With Bolna, enterprises get:

1. Full control over agent intelligence, tone, and workflows
2. Cost efficiency at scale with smart routing across providers and price points
3. Enterprise-grade performance on latency, interruptions, multi-language, and multi-accent understanding
one_liner: Voice AI to enable India's next billion

name: Hyperspell
long_description:
Hyperspell (YC F25) gives AI agents memory.

It connects to tools like Slack, Gmail, Notion, and Drive so agents can recall, reason, and remember across company knowledge. Developers use Hyperspell’s API to turn disconnected agents into AI coworkers that understand their work. Conor and Manu founded Hyperspell after building their own workplace agent and seeing how limited AI is without memory. They have over 15 years of experience in machine learning and have scaled API-based products to $30M ARR.
one_liner: Memory for AI Agents.

name: Scoop
long_description: We’re building AI agents that speed up drug trials by automating the manual consolidation and document prep required for every IND submission. Today, biotechs spend months stitching together reports from contractors and internal teams just to file and get to their first-in-human trial.
one_liner: AI agents that speed up drug trials, starting with IND filings

name: Aspect
long_description:
When footage comes off a camera, media content teams spend hours organizing their project, syncing across business tools, assembling rough drafts, reviewing for changes, and sending the right links to the right people and stakeholders.

Aspect is an AI platform that understands a team’s video library and business workflows better than humans. The platform automates the entire enterprise production process, so  instead of managing corporate back-office tasks, creatives can focus on what they love while companies achieve higher ROI on their content.
one_liner: AI platform for enterprise media content

name: Deeptrace
long_description:
At Deeptrace, we’re building AI agents that investigate and resolve production alerts end-to-end. Deeptrace cuts through the noise, pinpoints root causes instantly, and gives engineering teams back what they need most: the freedom to build instead of firefighting.

In production, we're already seeing a reduction in time spent triaging, investigating, and resolving alerts with some of the fastest growing companies in the world.
one_liner: AI agents for on-call

name: Locus
long_description:
We make your agents pay.

As agents evolve from tools into dependable, autonomous actors, they’ll need the ability to execute open-ended workflows end-to-end.

This inevitably means payments: accessing paywalled data, transacting for services or with other specialist agents. But autonomy requires guardrails. Businesses and developers will need a way to ensure their agents only spend how much and on what they’re supposed to.

The machine economy is coming, and Locus (YC F25) is building the connector businesses will need to participate. We connect agents securely to funds, letting you define permissions and limits for every transaction. Each payment is traceable, auditable, and fully reconcilable with your existing financial stack.
one_liner: Payment infrastructure for agents

name: Alt-X
long_description:
Private markets are still opaque, manual, and locked inside Excel. Every year, trillions of dollars in venture, real-estate, and private-equity capital are deployed through diligence processes that haven’t changed in decades. Analysts spend hours parsing PDFs and spreadsheets just to understand what a company or property is worth.

Alt-X is building the data and AI infrastructure layer for alternative assets — a system that ingests unstructured deal materials, normalizes the data, and generates institutional-grade analysis in seconds. Whether it’s a private-company dataroom or a real-estate offering memorandum, Alt-X extracts key KPIs like ARR, growth, NOI, IRR, and cap rate, then produces investor-ready dashboards and reports automatically.

Our platform reduces deal evaluation timelines by up to 73%, saves 30–50 analyst hours per deal, and enables teams to screen 4× more opportunities with the same headcount. By automating KPI extraction, benchmarking, and underwriting, Alt-X transforms diligence from a manual bottleneck into a scalable process.

This hasn’t been done at scale because private-market data is fragmented across formats and asset classes. Alt-X’s parsing engine unifies this chaos into a structured schema — the backbone for cross-asset underwriting, KPI dashboards, and automated risk scoring.

Our first wedge is real estate and private equity, where underwriting is slowest and most manual. We’re already piloting with family offices and private funds managing over $200 million in assets, paying $1K–$5K per month to automate deal screening and valuation.

The opportunity is massive: over $1.4 trillion in new private-equity and real-estate deals are underwritten globally each year, with $25–30 billion spent on diligence and analytics. Yet over 90% of this still happens manually. Alt-X’s mission is to become the operating system for private-market investing — the Bloomberg Terminal of the AI era.
one_liner: AI Diligence Tools for Private Investors

name: Caddy
long_description:
We are building Siri for work, but it actually works. Caddy turns your voice into the next computing interface. It understands what’s on your screen and your intent, so work gets done while you stay in flow.

Say “create a Linear ticket and share it to Slack” and Caddy handles it instantly in the background.

Caddy’s founders previously led product and design for Loom’s AI suite and core products. We believe the next era of computing will be powered by voice, where computers understand what you say and what’s on your screen so work happens naturally.
one_liner: Control all your work apps with your voice

name: Sorce
long_description: Tinder for Jobs. Swipe right, AI applies on your behalf.

name: The Context Company
long_description:
Ship reliable agents with confidence.

AI agents often fail quietly, picking the wrong tools, looping, hallucinating, and more. The Context Company tells developers when and exactly where their agents fail so issues can be uncovered and fixed fast.

It combines traditional observability across traces, tool calls, latency, and costs with the ability to uncover silent failures that standard monitoring misses.

Get started with less than 10 lines of code.
one_liner: Observability for AI agents to help developers fix failures fast

name: Dari
long_description:
An automation platform where users can reliably automate web workflows using natural language prompts.

We handle two-factor authentication and deterministic playback of workflows, ensuring your workflows don't break.

name: Lunavo
long_description:
We build AI that runs carrier operations.

Lunavo is the AI assistant for carriers. It plugs directly into their existing toolstack, understands their processes, and monitors all incoming data and requests. Lunavo runs end-to-end backoffice operations, handling repetitive tasks, resolving issues autonomously, and escalating only what matters.

Lunavo helps carriers scale operations without scaling headcount.
one_liner: Lunavo is the AI assistant for carriers.

name: Soren
long_description:
Soren builds autonomous agents to replace human engineers on manual AI evaluation tasks.

Evals are essential for building reliable AI systems, yet they remain incredibly time-consuming. Teams spend countless hours maintaining their evals and digging through piles of logs and traces to debug their systems. At scale, this level of manual work simply isn’t sustainable.

Soren changes that with powerful agents that work alongside your team. They reason across test cases and logs to pinpoint root causes, then run targeted experiments to surface better-performing solutions. New test cases are added whenever new behaviors are detected, so engineers can stop doing ad-hoc maintenance.

We're building a future where AI handles the work and humans simply provide oversight.
one_liner: The AI engineer for evals.

name: Norra
long_description:
Nursing facilities are bleeding money and staff time due to operational chaos. They have zero visibility into their equipment and operations, leading to over-purchasing, equipment failures, and nurses spending hours hunting for things instead of caring for patients.

Norra creates a real-time view of everything happening in the facility. We use AI and autonomous tracking to transform operational chaos into proactive decision-making. Instead of reacting to equipment failures or over-purchasing because they can't find what they own, facilities get actionable insights that prevent waste before it happens.
one_liner: AI Equipment Operations Platform for Nursing Facilites

name: Kaigo Health
long_description: Kaigo Health provides an AI-powered outpatient care management platform that automates and scales remote care management for Medicare patients including post-discharge followups, ongoing check-ins, and monitoring. Using phone calls as an age-friendly interface, we aggregate patient responses, voice biomarkers, and remote patient monitoring data for powerful preventative and proactive healthcare.
one_liner: AI outpatient care workforce

name: Koyal
long_description:
Koyal is an Agentic AI Filmmaking Platform that allows you to seamlessly convert script or audio into personalized, visually compelling stories. We’re a team from Carnegie Mellon, MIT and Meta, with experience in AI video generation.

https://koyal.ai builds directly upon our published research at the AI conference NeurIPS in December. We’ve been covered in the international press for our patented secure personalization protocol CHARCHA: the genAI captcha.

Announcement: https://x.com/meh_agarwal/status/1965866965425348687
Demo: https://x.com/meh_agarwal/status/1965137062119752099


We currently have paid pilots with the biggest global music labels, podcasts and production houses, and just launched our public beta at beta.koyal.ai

We recently concluded a pilot with Universal Music and T-Series (world’s largest music label) alongside Bollywood production houses like Maddock Entertainment, and Collective Artists Network! As part of that, we launched 5 music videos for Grammy and Oscar winning artists like A R Rahman, Ricky Kej and Shankar Mahadevan all crossing 1.5 million views!

We've recently built SOTA capabilities in (i) multilingual script to audio to video, (ii) Agentic lip-sync with dynamic movement & (iii) Multi-character consistency.
one_liner: Agentic AI Filmmaking Platform

name: PlayVision
long_description:
PlayVision is the AI Moneyball for Sports: the future for scouting, recruiting, and playing the game.

Basketball teams upload their practices or games, and PlayVision uses AI and computer vision to automatically tag and analyze the film, giving coaches and scouts 10 times the information on their players and their opponents. PlayVision also uses algorithms to rank every single college and professional basketball player in the country with over 40 different metrics from tracking and play-by-play data. 

Check out our website at withplayvision.ai, and follow our instagram @playvisionai!
one_liner: AI Moneyball for Sports

name: Land.dev
long_description:
America has a land problem. 

We are spending more, and building less. 

American real estate developers waste their time navigating data scattered across 23,000 jurisdictions. An apartment builder must check dozens of different databases, parse hundreds of PDFs, and still might miss a critical detail buried in an ancient document.

We use AI to normalize the country’s land data into one source of truth, so developers can focus on building.
one_liner: Solving America's Land Problem with AI

name: Iris
long_description:
Iris connects all your calendars and inboxes in one place with a built in personal assistant. It connects with Gmail, Google Calendar, Maps, and more to understand your context - what you’re working on, who you’re meeting, and where you need to be - and intelligently organizes your time around what actually matters. 

Unlike assistants that just schedule events, Iris learns your rhythm and automates your workflow: drafting emails, moving meetings, blocking focus time, and coordinating across accounts, all with your approval. 

We’re building the next generation of personal AI, one that keeps you ahead.
one_liner: All your calendars and inboxes, powered by an intelligent assistant.

name: Veria Labs
long_description:
Veria Labs is developing AI agents that hack better than the best human hackers. Founded by members of the #1 US competitive hacking team, we've already manually found critical bugs in AI tools, operating systems, fintech and billion dollar crypto exchanges. 

Now we're scaling that expertise through AI-native security tooling that operates faster than human researchers while finding deeper, more complex vulnerabilities that traditional tools miss.
one_liner: Continuous AI pentesting that finds and fixes vulnerabilities

name: Velum Labs
long_description:
Velum is an open-source firewall for content-level access control across documents, databases, and applications. Admins define policies, and we apply them in real time across your entire stack to control what each recipient sees.

Our firewall sits between your data sources and consumers (LLMs, users, vendors), enforcing policies on every request. We understand meaning in text, documents, and databases to detect sensitive information based on your policies, then apply recipient-specific controls without blocking workflows.

Create policies in natural language. Teams write rules that define what's sensitive and who should access it, and Velum enforces them consistently across all systems. When authorization changes, we can reveal tokenized data just-in-time for approved recipients, maintaining both security and utility.

We integrate directly into your existing infrastructure. For AI workflows, we intercept prompts, responses, and retrievals to prevent sensitive information from leaking into or out of models. For enterprise systems like Salesforce, SAP, or Workday, we extend policy enforcement to exports, reports, and syncs.

Velum is designed for scale and compliance. We provide encryption and structure-preserving tokenization for high-throughput pipelines, with multi-cloud deployment options and configurable data residency per tenant to meet your compliance requirements.
one_liner: Firewall that controls access to information across AI and humans

name: Questom
long_description: A unified AI workforce for wholesale that handles every workflow from quote to delivery and becomes the system of record that replaces CRM and ERP entirely.
one_liner: Agentic OS for Wholesalers

name: Cranston AI
long_description:
Cranston is a full stack AI accounting firm automating the $200b market for accounting labor. Our software automates reconciliation, tax compliance and financial analysis for startups & SMBs. We pull in context from all your company's apps & data, connect to existing systems of record and handle repetitive accounting work.

Our team is deep in the accounting space. Sean spent 5 years building an ERP after dropping out of Stanford and Max spent 5 years building an accounting firm that did every accounting workflow you can imagine on top of ERPs.
one_liner: Full stack AI for accounting and finance

name: Hypercubic
long_description:
Hypercubic is an AI-native maintenance and modernization platform for COBOL and mainframes.

We help enterprises understand and preserve their mission-critical legacy systems. About 70% of the Fortune 500 companies still rely on them to run their core business applications in banking, insurance, telecom, airlines, retail, and more.

These systems, originally built in the 1960s–90s, still power trillions in global infrastructure today but have become increasingly opaque as original developers retire or leave the workforce. 

We're laying the foundation to autonomously maintain and modernize these legacy systems to future-proof the backbone of the global economy.


Learn more at hypercubic.ai
one_liner: AI to maintain and modernize COBOL/mainframes.

name: Nessie
long_description:
Nessie is Perplexity for your mind, turning your scattered AI conversations and notes into a personal knowledge base. It's a thinking partner that lets you instantly search your entire history of ideas, synthesize them into new insights, and watch your knowledge build on itself over time.

Who it's for: AI-native thinkers—founders, researchers, and writers—who believe their best ideas should compound.

We are two Yale CS grads and former Amazon engineers building the tool we needed for ourselves. We combine Anna's research on enhancing LLM reasoning with knowledge graphs, and Tiger's lifelong passion for building products, which started with shipping an Android app with 70k+ downloads at age 13.

Nessie was born from our shared obsession - we were using AI to push the limits of our own thinking, but the current tools couldn't keep up. Brilliant insights were getting lost in endless chat histories, and the context was constantly fragmented.

We realized the problem wasn't just about memory; it was that the medium for AI-native thought didn't exist yet. The chat window is a place to ask questions, not a place to build on ideas.

We're building Nessie to be that medium—your personal context layer, designed to amplify human thinking and give you agency over your own knowledge.
one_liner: Perplexity for your mind

name: Wardstone
long_description: Wardstone is a space defense-tech company developing next-generation capabilities to protect the United States and its allies from missiles and other space-based threats. We design, build, and deploy satellites equipped with space-based interceptors to kinetically counter hypersonic and ballistic missiles.

former_names: I purchased precedents.ai, will found a corp w/ Clerky in 2 weeks once the domain transfer is confirmed

Additionally, our fleet of AI-powered agents will continuously analyze thousands of mobile apps, gathering design insights and identifying growth opportunities + actionable product improvements.

long_description: We work with the world's most brilliant mathematicians to design RL environments that enable LLMs to achieve state-of-the-art model performance.

name: Flick
long_description:
Flick is an AI filmmaking software that lets people create Hollywood-level short films completely using AI end-to-end.

There are many AI tools that can give you 8-second casual clips to post on social media, but when it comes to creating truly high-quality films with coherent storylines, consistent characters, and cinematic aesthetics, they don’t come close due to their lack of flexibility, creative control, and fragmented creative flow.

Founded by an award-winning filmmaker and a founding engineer at Instagram, Flick defines an interface specifically designed for native AI filmmaking that feels natural and enables end-to-end creative flows. Think of Flick as Figma for AI filmmaking.

There are 4 complete AI short films created using Flick that got 20+ awards in international film festivals already and our early creator residency community are generating several AI short films every week.

We are also building a community where we produce our own AI films as well as collaborating with other well-known filmmakers to share their “behind-the-scenes” workflows as resuable templates to inspire users in our community. We not only build product, we also build world-class content.

The whole film industry will be revolutionized by AI and our goal is to be “the product” that defines this category.
one_liner: End-to-end AI filmmaking software.

name: Semble AI
long_description:
Semble AI automates fire-life-safety design. Instantly generate code-compliant device layouts, bills of materials (BOMs), and quote estimates. Replace guesswork with AI - getting it right the first time and allowing teams to produce bids in minutes, not weeks.

No missed devices or materials. 
No regulation lookups. 
No back-and-forth with permitting authorities.
No overrun cost surprises.

Semble AI is the new standard for fire-life-safety.
one_liner: Autonomous fire and life-safety systems engineer

name: Mod AI
long_description:
We build AI agents that automate the accounts payable process for enterprises.

Designed to imitate accounts payable clerks, our AI agents read emails and find valid invoices, extract data from any document format, perform matching with purchase orders and receipts, route invoices organization-wide for approval, and sync directly with your ERP or accounting system.

That why we're building two things. First, Elastic Cloud: a managed platform that automatically finds the cheapest GPUs across all providers, handles spot instance preemption, and cuts compute costs by up to 80%. Second, automatic kernel optimization that makes training code run faster by modeling hardware topology, often beating hand-tuned implementations.

The problem is that getting high performance across different hardware is genuinely hard. NVIDIA's CUDA moat exists because writing fast kernels requires deep expertise. Most teams either accept vendor lock-in or hire expensive kernel engineers. Our goal is to break the CUDA moat.

The compute bottleneck is the biggest constraint on AI progress. NVIDIA can't manufacture enough GPUs, and their monopoly keeps prices astronomical. Meanwhile, AMD, Google, and Amazon are shipping capable alternative hardware that nobody uses because the software is too hard. We're breaking that moat. If we succeed, anyone will be able to train state-of-the-art models without thinking past their PyTorch code.

long_description: JSX Tool is a browser extension that hooks into your React project, so you can easily locate any React component and file with just a click. This gives developers the ability to articulate visual requests to LLMs that without JSX Tool, are either vague or cumbersome to communicate in English and code snippets. On top of that JSX Tool is a full featured IDE tailored specifically for React Development, so users never have to leave the context of their browser when developing React code.
one_liner: AI-First In-Browser IDE for React Development
